Package edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.data

Class Student

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.data.Student
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Identifiable, java.lang.Comparable<Student>
    public class Student
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Student>, Identifiable
    A student is comparable and identifiable. Students have a first name, last name, id number, number of credit hours, gpa, and unityID. This class has the constructor, getters, setters, compareTo(), equals(), hashCode(), and toString() method for the Student.
    Author:
    Dr. King and Amit Prakash

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo​(Student s1)
        This is a comparison students' first names, last names, and ID numbers. This is overridden to provide a specific comparison of the student objects according to last name, first name, and id in that order.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Student>
        Parameters:
        s1 - The student object to be compared to the object called on this object.
        Returns:
        position indicator integer: This is the value that separates this object from the Students, given 0 if they are the same, a negative integer if before, a positive integer if after.
